k%20after%20us%20when%20they're%20in%20a%20favorable%20swing%2C%26quot%3B%20Morse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20that%20eating%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20plant%20foods%2C%20such%20as%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20whole%20grains%2C%20legumes%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20seeds%2C%20supports%20a%20diverse%20gut%20microbiome.%20These%20foods%20all%20contain%20fiber%2C%20which%20feeds%20the%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20bacteria%20in%20the%20gut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c6abdd98-938c-4c79-90d3-b4b3d57cc358%5C%22%3EThe%20immune%20system%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2080%25%20of%20the%20body's%20immune%20cells%20are%20found%20just%20outside%20the%20gut%20lining%2C%20Spector%20said.%20So%20your%20gut%20bacteria%20and%20the%20chemicals%20they%20produce%20regularly%20interact%20with%20the%20immune%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20interaction%20helps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-gut-health-gut-gardening-brain-immune-system-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btrain%26quot%3B%20the%20immune%20system%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20know%20when%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20threat%20and%20when%20everything%20is%20OK%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20a%20healthy%20microbiome%20have%20a%20thicker%20protective%20layer%20that%20stops%20waste%20products%20and%20microbes%20from%20crossing%20over%20the%20gut%20lining%20into%20the%20immune%20tissues%2C%20which%20reduces%20the%20likelihood%20of%20inflammation%2C%20one%20of%20the%20body's%20natural%20defenses%20against%20infection%2C%20Spector%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcute%20inflammation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20redness%2C%20warmth%2C%20swelling%2C%20and%20pain%20we%20feel%20around%20an%20injury%20%E2%80%94%20is%20healthy.%20But%20when%20inflammation%20lingers%20on%20for%20too%20long%20it%20becomes%20chronic%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20white%20blood%20cells%20attacking%20healthy%20tissues%2C%20according%20to%20Harvard%20Medical%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChronic%20inflammation%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20various%20diseases%2C%20such%20as%20heart%20disease%2C%20diabetes%2C%20cancer%2C%20arthritis%2C%20Crohn's%20disease%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fulcerative-colitis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eulcerative%20colitis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d76e467-c0f6-470a-b378-dc457c5c3d42%5C%22%3EMental%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20strong%20evidence%20that%20a%20good%20diet%20is%20linked%20to%20better%20mental%20health%2C%20brain%20health%2C%20and%20mood%2C%20likely%20because%20it%20promotes%20a%20healthy%20gut%20microbiome%2C%20Spector%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gut%20and%20the%20brain%20are%20in%20constant%20communication%20with%20each%20other%20via%20multiple%20pathways%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fvagus-nerve-exercises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evagus%20nerve%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Church%20said.%20This%20bidirectional%20connection%20is%20known%20as%20the%20gut-brain%20axis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20about%20that%20high-pressure%20situation%20when%20you%20have%20to%20go%20for%20a%20job%20interview%20or%20go%20on%20a%20date.%20We%20often%20experience%20being%20both%20lightheaded%20and%20having%20weird%20sensations%20in%20our%20stomach%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChurch%20likes%20to%20describe%20the%20gut%20and%20the%20brain%20as%20%26quot%3BBFFs%26quot%3B%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20go%20hand%20in%20hand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20change%20to%20the%20gut%20microbiome%20will%20disrupt%20communication%20with%20the%20brain%2C%20leading%20to%20changes%20in%20mood%2C%20cognition%2C%20and%20emotional%20regulation%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20easiest%20way%20to%20support%20the%20gut-brain%20connection%20is%20by%20eating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-30-plants-a-week-gut-health-easier-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20diet%20rich%20in%20fiber%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%2C%20and%20antioxidants%2C%20and%20cutting%20back%20on%20processed%20foods%2C%20added%20sugars%2C%20artificial%20sweeteners%2C%20and%20alcohol%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENumerous%20studies%20suggest%20that%20people%20with%20depression%20and%20anxiety%20often%20have%20different%20gut%20microbes%20to%20those%20who%20don't.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20depressed%20person%20might%20have%20lower%20levels%20of%20certain%20beneficial%20bacteria%20and%20higher%20levels%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-diy-poop-transplants-got-brother-acne-fecal-microbiota-transplant-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotentially%20harmful%20bacteria%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db5c1418-0e4f-46b8-b108-7dfa527d23cd%5C%22%3EHormonal%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHormones%20are%20substances%20produced%20by%20glands%20that%20act%20as%20messengers%2C%20letting%20the%20body%20know%20when%20it's%20time%20to%20do%20certain%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGut%20bacteria%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20maintaining%20a%20healthy%20hormonal%20balance%20in%20the%20body%2C%20Dr.%20Max%20Nieuwdorp%2C%20an%20endocrinologist%20who%20researches%20the%20role%20of%20the%20gut%20microbiome%20in%20hormonal%20processes%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20involved%20in%20the%20release%20and%20production%20of%20dozens%20of%20different%20hormones%20and%20can%20influence%20the%20brain%20via%20the%20central%20nervous%20system%2C%20according%20to%20his%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Power%20of%20Hormones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20producing%20serotonin%20and%20dopamine%2C%20which%20are%20essential%20for%20regulating%20mood%20and%20anxiety%2C%20Church%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208a1fc9b-8dc5-4029-af43-62f3a4a9dd59%5C%22%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20gut%20health%20likely%20stretch%20even%20further%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20lots%20of%20emerging%20research%20that%20suggests%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20gut%20microbiome%20extends%20even%20further%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGut%20health%20might%20influence%20the%20lungs%2C%20kidney%2C%20mouth%2C%20gums%2C%20and%20skin%2C%20as%20well%20as%20bone%20density%20and%20sleep%20quality%2C%20Church%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20also%20investigating%20the%20direct%20links%20between%20gut%20health%20and%20a%20range%20of%20diseases%2C%20Spector%20said%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorectal-cancer-high-mortality-young-people-signs-symptoms-disease-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20and%20metabolic%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgut-health-boost-overall-digestion-better-moods-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720867382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668e71ca3598be27b3454df4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgut-health-boost-overall-digestion-better-moods-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gut%20health%20is%20a%20buzzy%20topic%20right%20now%2C%20and%20for%20good%20reason.%20Experts%20break%20down%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20take%20care%20of%20your%20gut%20microbiome.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40businessinsider.com%20(Kim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgut-health-boost-overall-digestion-better-moods-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Babar%20hilariously%20trolled%20for%20%E2%80%98gaffe%E2%80%99%20in%20Anderson's%20retirement%20post%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720866778000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.