lage%20and%20found%20jobs%20as%20security%20guards%20and%20drivers%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Pune.%20But%20when%20they%20heard%20about%20the%20success%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F199310%2Fmumbai-man-revives-traditional-ponds-vasai-virar-water-hero-inspiring-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20pond%20revival%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20started%20making%20plans%20to%20return%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDismantling%20social%20constructs%20was%20exciting%20for%20Tiwari%20and%20his%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20crux%20on%20which%20their%20water%20project%20had%20been%20founded%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EGaav%20ka%20paani%20gaav%20mein%2C%20khet%20ka%20paani%20khet%20mein%20%3C%2Fem%3E(The%20water%20of%20the%20village%20should%20remain%20in%20the%20village%2C%20and%20the%20water%20of%20the%20fields%20should%20be%20restricted%20to%20the%20fields.)%20To%20ensure%20this%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20started%20desilting%20many%20ponds%20around%20Bundelkhand%20across%20the%20villages%20of%20Marka%2C%20Pindaran%2C%20Gahbra%2C%20Jhalokhar%2C%20Mohnipur%20among%20others.%20We%20also%20started%20building%20troughs%20of%20two%20feet%20height%20around%20every%20field%20so%20that%20the%20rainwater%20could%20collect%20in%20this%20and%20be%20used%20for%20farming%20purposes%20even%20after%20the%20monsoons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Foa--noZyZ1g%3Fsi%3DPCal_G3LmdeNRJu6%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiwari%20and%20his%20team%20also%20organised%3Cem%3E%20paani%20chaupals%3C%2Fem%3E%20(water%20awareness%20sessions)%20where%20they%20challenged%20the%20villagers%20to%20question%20their%20water%20usage%2C%20and%20water-saving%20techniques.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20conducted%20over%20300%20of%20these%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tiwari%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20started%20making%20water%20friends%20who%20we%20call%20%E2%80%98jal%20mitras%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%20Sharing%20more%20about%20this%20concept%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20work%20is%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20respective%20villages%2C%20research%20water%20bodies%20and%20their%20capacities%2C%20work%20with%20tank%20management%20committees%20to%20see%20which%20ponds%20can%20be%20revived%20and%20create%20awareness%20about%20water%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Tiwari%20has%20a%20network%20of%205%2C000%20water%20friends%20across%20Bundelkhand.%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20not%20be%20around%20forever.%20I%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20that%20my%20work%20continues%20even%20if%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Through%20the%20efforts%20and%20Tiwari%20and%20his%20friends%2C%20the%20Bajrang%20Sagar%20pond%20filled%20up%20with%20rainwater%20that%20lasted%20for%20a%20year%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-6-1720083929-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3